  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The APPROPRIATE study will compare differences in functional capacity (peak VO2) between
      chronotropically incompetent patients randomized to receive rate responsive pacing driven by
      either the minute ventilation (respiration-based) sensor or an accelerometer (motion-based).
    </textblock>
